1 Questions

  • Negative finalGold values (-1, -2)?
  • Age variable Age_Enroll?
  • Covariates for all 6 phenotypes
  • Related individuals?

2 Variable Names

2.1 Traits

Phenotype Used variables Other variables
COPD status finalGold
FEV1 FEV1pp_utah FEV1_utah, pre_FEV1, deltaFEV1, BDR_pct_FEV1
FVC FVCpp_utah FVC_utah, pre_FVC, deltaFVC, BDR_pct_FVC
FEV1/FVC ratio FEV1_FVC_utah pre_FEV1_FVC
Percent emphysema pctEmph_Slicer
TLC TLCpp_race_adjusted

Comments from Michael:

  • COPD status, finalGold: 0 means control; finalgold 2,3,4 means case
  • FEV1, FEV1_utah, FEV1pp_utah: This needs adjustment for age, sex, height. Percent predicted is FEV1pp_utah
  • FVC, FVC_utah , FVCpp_utah: these are post-bronchodilator
  • Percent emphysema, pctEmph_Slicer: We usually log this value and include scanner and current smoking (smokcignow) as covariates.
  • TLC, TLCpp_race_adjusted: this is already adjusted for race, and body size

2.2 Covariates

Covariate Used variable Other variables
age Age_Enroll CopdAge
gender gender
center ccenter
packs/year ATS_PackYears
ever smoked EverSmokedCig
smoking now SmokCigNow
height Height_CM

5 Correlations (spearman)

  • Spearman correlations are computed.
  • No special treatment for finalGold variable.

The traits are ordered by the hierarchical clustering.

5.1 Correlations + more details

Traits order:

  • Age_Enroll
  • acs_global
  • finalGold
  • FEV1pp_utah
  • FVCpp_utah
  • FEV1_FVC_utah
  • log_pctEmph_Slicer
  • TLCpp_race_adjusted

6 Kumars model

Model:

FEV1pp_utah ~ acs_global + gender + c_Age_Enroll + c_log_ATS_PackYears +  
    c_Height_CM + c_Height_CM2 + c_BMI + (1 | ccenter)
